15/03/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano on Saturday (13 March) condemned a grenade attack on Kosovo President Ibrahim Rugova's home.
A hand grenade thrown Friday at the presidential residence in Pristina slightly injured a guard and caused minor damage.
In a phone call to Rugova, Nano also reconfirmed Albania's support for the democratisation process in Kosovo.
(ATA, KosovaLive - 13/03/04)
